id: records/material-time
title: "material time"
kind: record-protocol
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-01

definition: >
  Material time is the inspectable record of what actually happened: files,
  tools, accesses, backups, commits, external surfaces, decisions, costs, and
  proof receipts.

why_it_matters: >
  Movement needs memory that can be checked. Material records keep the system
  from relying only on interpretation, vibes, or model narration.

record_types:
  - file access
  - llm/tool access
  - github access
  - backup
  - commit or branch
  - external account or service
  - proof receipt
  - next-move rationale

rule: >
  If an access, backup, or external surface changes what the next move should
  be, record it.

proof:
  source:
    - yawn.yawn
    - core/yawn-space.yawn
  status: seed-backed
